  "title": "CNC Lathe Machinist / Programmer",
  "description": "<p>Knowledge to Mastercam & Solidwork , Program for CNC Milling & Lathe</p><p>· Read and understand engineering drawings, specifications, GD&T, CNC machine setup and process routing.</p><p>· Liaise with production team and engineers on the production information.</p><p>· Translate instructions into codes for machines to perform accurate functions.</p><p>· Prepare machine setup for test runs to ensure machine outputs are according to specifications.</p><p>· Set machines to complete full cycles to fabricate large number of parts.</p><p>· Create solid models using the CAD/ CAM software with precision according to the drawings.</p><p>· Coordinate with process engineers and machine stop technicians/ supervisors to create and validate machining programs.</p><p>· Supervise the task execution and inspect and measure finished products to ensure that measurements are complied with.</p><p>· Document the CNC program process and maintain the revision change according to change management process.</p><p><u>Requirements</u></p><p>· Professional certificate in Precision Engineering or relevant field.</p><p>· Minimum 1 years in programming experience.</p><p>· Excellent knowledge in handling, programming & setting up of CNC machines.</p><p>· Able to read engineering drawings and understand the GD&T.</p><p>· Proficiency of at least one CAD/ CAM software with 3D modelling.</p><p>· Able to communicate in English.</p><p>· Good interpersonal skills.</p><p>· Keen attention to details.</p><p>· Ability to perform work accurately and thoroughly.</p>",
